Debevoise Ave., at the N.E. corner of Maspeth Ave., housed the employees of Peter Cooper, who conducted a glue factory in the rear of these houses. (Cooper Park and Cooper Union were named in his memory.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
